"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM comments \n     WHERE PostId = (SELECT Id FROM posts WHERE Title = 'Clustering 1D data')) AS CommentCount,\n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM posts \n     WHERE ParentId = (SELECT Id FROM posts WHERE Title = 'Clustering 1D data')) AS AnswerCount;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the number of comments and answers associated with the post titled 'Clustering 1D data'. It uses subqueries to first find the post ID with the specified title and then counts the related comments and answers."